1. **File:** `branch-chat/src/lib/db.ts`, function `connectDB()`, lines 10-17
   **Issue:** If `mongoose.connect()` rejects, the rejected promise is permanently cached. All subsequent calls return the same rejected promise — the app cannot recover without a process restart.
   **Fix:** Wrap `cached.conn = await cached.promise;` in a try/catch. In the catch block, set `cached.promise = null` then re-throw the error. This allows the next call to `connectDB()` to retry the connection.
   ```typescript
   export async function connectDB() {
     if (cached.conn) return cached.conn;
     if (!cached.promise) {
       cached.promise = mongoose.connect(MONGODB_URI);
     }
     try {
       cached.conn = await cached.promise;
     } catch (err) {
       cached.promise = null;
       throw err;
     }
     return cached.conn;
   }
   ```
